<component type="desktop-application">
    <id>com.samirsinha.Clemens</id>

    <name>Clemens</name>
    <summary>An Apple IIgs Emulator and Debugger written in C/C++ for Windows and Linux.</summary>
    <developer_name>Samir Sinha</developer_name>
    <update_contact>unknown_AT_samirsinha.com</update_contact>

    <metadata_license>MIT</metadata_license>
    <project_license>MIT</project_license>

    <url type="homepage">https://github.com/samkusin/clemens_iigs</url>
    <url type="faq">https://github.com/samkusin/clemens_iigs/wiki</url>

    <description>
        <p>
		The Clemens IIgs emulator is an attempt at writing a modern emulator
		for the Apple IIgs machine. Its design focuses on developers versus
		casual play, providing tools to debug IIgs applications at runtime. 
		My eventual goal is to provide a solid Apple IIgs backend and debugger 
		with a functional frontend.
        </p>
    </description>

